<subSubSection id="E1596C26F1839476F212809A1CE88E58" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="2679F67063DEEDF846B72BBC4D9263B4" pageNumber="1">
Members of the sisorid catfish genus 
<taxonomicName id="60EC97BC5C6DE401B36D53E295CEF92E" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:1C6AC061-0134-487B-9102-EFF719A47063" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sisoridae" genus="Pareuchiloglanis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pareuchiloglanis Pellegrin 1936:245" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Pareuchiloglanis Pellegrin, 1936</taxonomicName>
are rheophilic catfishes chiefly found in the headwaters of major river drainages throughout South and East Asia. They belong to the sisorid subfamily Glyptosterninae, a group distributed from the Caucasus to China, and have been distinguished from other members of the subfamily by the presence of homodont dentition arranged in narrow bands with sides not extending posteriorly.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="38C6E035549FFF140F291A6758740564" pageNumber="2">
The monophyly of 
<taxonomicName id="C72B1B61B95255507FF3B330A6399FA1" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:1C6AC061-0134-487B-9102-EFF719A47063" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sisoridae" genus="Pareuchiloglanis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pareuchiloglanis Pellegrin 1936:245" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Pareuchiloglanis</taxonomicName>
remains doubtful. He (1995, 1996) demonstrated the paraphyly of 
<taxonomicName id="993487849B1DA8A0ADA26D3708EBDF49" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:1C6AC061-0134-487B-9102-EFF719A47063" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sisoridae" genus="Pareuchiloglanis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pareuchiloglanis Pellegrin 1936:245" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Pareuchiloglanis</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="7AB8718C40B9ADAE54F62C15D14F7894" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:E68EC2A2-F2FB-48AE-BBCE-ABCFD9555304" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sisoridae" genus="Oreoglanis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Oreoglanis Smith 1933:70" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Oreoglanis</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="C9FC5E7D6C9534991C1A9B93D8A52F81" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:AC273B3A-FA06-469F-9A73-E1E5BD9033D6" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sisoridae" genus="Pseudexostoma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pseudexostoma Chu 1979:78, 81" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Pseudexostoma</taxonomicName>
(possibly with the inclusion of 
<taxonomicName id="5547AB6466852C6CC98CA63BE6CB3A16" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:03336E7C-2732-46B2-8FB4-12EAF8E099DD" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sisoridae" genus="Myersglanis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Myersglanis Hora &amp; Silas 1952:19" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Myersglanis</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="035B4CCC1AA1BA643E62F7F12E09EAE1" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:9E00F939-C85D-4350-ADE6-9DAC74966394" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sisoridae" genus="Parachiloglanis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Parachiloglanis Wu, He &amp; Chu 1981:76, 79" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Parachiloglanis</taxonomicName>
) and a rediagnosis of glyptosternine genera is badly needed. However, that is beyond the scope of this study, and the current definition of 
<taxonomicName id="C7CA96B5DE3ADDECD4F895908D7F3CB8" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:1C6AC061-0134-487B-9102-EFF719A47063" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sisoridae" genus="Pareuchiloglanis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pareuchiloglanis Pellegrin 1936:245" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Pareuchiloglanis</taxonomicName>
is used here.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A43B3618ABFD5A650503D2888B3618C8" pageNumber="2">
While examining material for a study on the phylogenetic relationships of glyptosternine genera, material from the Red River (Song Hong) drainage in northern Vietnam, and the Salween River (Nujiang) and Irrawaddy River drainages in southern China were found to belong to two undescribed species. The description of the Chinese material as 
<taxonomicName id="B789C4E0E83ADFB56E042D7F36D76FDC" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:7B7369B8-E382-4718-827C-4931C8F60FBB" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sisoridae" genus="Pareuchiloglanis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pareuchiloglanis macropterus Ng 2004:3" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="macropterus">Pareuchiloglanis macropterus</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="9BCEA177FE45AA8EA923DD0066067FF1" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and the Vietnamese material as 
<taxonomicName id="944BF2CB680B1587836A151DFB5CDF08" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:83B65CFA-1F1E-4A82-A9E6-0E2F4BEDF726" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sisoridae" genus="Pareuchiloglanis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pareuchiloglanis rhabdurus Ng 2004:7" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rhabdurus">P. rhabdurus</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="4C3801DFF0BAD3EF81674F27290E2442" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, brings the total number of currently accepted species in this genus to fifteen.
</paragraph>
